President Obama received an update on the ongoing response to the wildfires in Arizona and discussed the Administration's work with state and local officials to fight the fires. The U.S. Forest Service and FEMA have been in close contact with state and local emergency management officials and are monitoring the fire activity. The U.S. Forest Service is supporting state and local firefighting efforts and managing the fires through inter-agency teams. The Governor of Arizona requested Fire Management Assistance Grants for two fires, which were awarded on the same day. President Obama called Governor Jan Brewer to express his concerns and assure her of continued federal support. The President praised the efforts of local and state officials and asked the Governor to keep him updated on additional support needed.